category = 16
text = "Goldmask is the leader of the Ragblacks which is an infamous mafia group in Dalanet's politics, believed to be running the Two Powers behind the scenes. The origins, name and nationality of Goldmask are unknown as he isn't seen without his namesake. Despite being a feared man, Goldmask often wears a simple dark blue tunic, stockings and polished leather boots, quite similar attire to a Dal peasant. He still however stands out wherever he goes, with both crowds and guards parting in his stride, not only due to his mask but also his two prosthetic fists, made entirely of gold and malleable to Goldmask's potent earthmagic. He didn't always have hands full of gold, it was a necessity to rise to his prominence.

The history of the Ragblacks is one of ambition. Goldmask became a member at a young age, but even then had his mask and was capable of making gold at will, why did he join despite possessing essentialy infinite wealth? No one knows. It was a smalltime, ragtag group and Goldmask believed they could grow if not for the weak leadership. Schwana, was a cautious and seemingly cowardly leader, even if given the opportunity to strike rich she preferred to go for easy pickings. When one day she was found dead with a spike of gold through her gullet the members accepted the change in leadership with few qualms. To solidify his position, Goldmask cut off his own hands in front of the men and replaced them with gold. His ascension began a change for the Ragblacks, they went after more expensive carriages and would leave the mark on each of their robberies, a golden spike typically in the noble's throat. The Seven Pillars and Two Powers were outraged and afraid they would look weak if they couldn't stop these robbers. Eventually, after Goldmask had his fun, he struck a deal with Gotwaf Toolich, one of the Two Powers, for ceasing his criminal activities he was given a spot as one of the Seven Pillars. Of course Goldmask never shows up and often sends an established member of the Ragblacks, or a novice if he is feeling particularly whimsiful.

Goldmask's fighting style involves quick manipulations of his golden hands. He is capable of protruding a sharp spike from the palm of his hand for close-quarters combat, a defensive disk from the top or even transforming his fist into a handcannon that shoots golden bullets. Needless to say, he is also capable of other forms of Earthmagic, but he considers them lesser than his gold manipulation. Goldmask is also known for possessing a very strong bubble, not in range but potency, often capable of restricting lesser mages by advancing close and restricting their casting. Never, not even in the most dire situations he has found himself in, will Goldmask transform his mask. He treats it with an almost religious devotion and brutally executes anyone that damages it when fighting him, even fellow bandit rivals will not dare aim for it when clashing with Goldmask.

The leader of the Ragblacks and one of the Seven Pillar continues to rise in power, some believe his aspiration is to become one of the Two Powers but his closest associates in the Ragblacks know different. Goldmask aims to fold the Two Powers into one and place himself at the top. Careful manueveuring over the last decade have slowly brought him closer to accomplishing this, he has secretly caused incidents in Dalanet that require the Seven Pillars to require his bandit expertise more. When Goldmask was first given the position of a Pillar it was seen as an appeasement, but he has now become a core part of the Seven Pillars. By his predictions, a few years, the right spike and the right words will ensure his position as one of the Two Powers and from there it's only a matter of time.

NOTES:
Two Powers - Kings of Dalenet
Seven Pillars - Councilmen, i dont think they have specific duties and some never show up cough Goldmask
the clothing sentence took literally 10 mins
Dal = Dalanetian
"
id = 31
name = "Goldmask"
